<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-638-178  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 638 178.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  July 9 1990 n308 p41(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Getting clearer. (Regional Bells move ahead with AdvancedIntelligent Network implementation) (CLose Up)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bushaus, Dawn.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Three of the Bell Regional holding companies are planning to testad roll out Advanced Intelligent Network services.andP;  Ameritech,Bell Atlantic and BellSouth will be testing AIN next year withsome of their largest customers.andP;  The goal of AIN is to provide alayered service control architecture for the signaling system 7protocol.andP;  This moves the control of calls from the switch to theservice control point (SCP), giving the telephone companiesgreater control over the rapid deployment of the design, test anddeployment of customized communications applications.andP;  Eventually,the AIN architecture will enable customers to enter the networkand design their own customized applications.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Information Technologies Corp. (products)Bell Atlantic Corp. (products)BellSouth Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    AIT; BLS; BEL.andO;Topic:     Bell Regional Holding CompaniesStrategic PlanningCommunications ApplicationsNetwork ArchitectureSignaling System 7 (Computer network protocol)Telephone Companies.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>